comments: Oubre Jr. (PHI) initiates contact with Jokic's (DEN) arm during the drive and affects Jokic's SQBR. A non-shooting foul is correctly assessed as the illegal contact occurs prior to the upward shooting motion on a play that ends outside the LDB.
Reed (PHI) establishes himself in Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

Jokic (DEN) hooks Oubre Jr.'s (PHI) arm during the drive, which affects Oubre Jr.'s SQBR. The illegal contact by Jokic occurs prior to Oubre Jr.'s gather and a non-shooting foul is correctly assessed.
Morris Sr. (PHI) and Jokic (DEN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
House Jr. (PHI) legally contests Jokic's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (DEN) deflects the loose ball away prior to any incidental follow-through contact with Oubre Jr. (PHI) during the rebound.
Murray (DEN) legally contests Morris Sr.'s (PHI) jump shot attempt.
Reed (PHI) makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) arm, which dislodges Jokic as he secures the rebound.
Batum (PHI) commits a take foul on Caldwell-Pope (DEN). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Beverley (PHI) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes two legal steps prior to releasing his pass.
Murray (DEN) legally contests and cleanly blocks Morris Sr.'s (PHI) jump shot attempt.
